<doc id="160" url="https://en.wikivoyage.org/wiki?curid=160" title="Achill Island">
<h1>Achill Island</h1>
&lt;templatestyles src="Pagebanner/styles.css"/&gt;
♡❤♡Achill Island♡❤♡ is the largest island off the &lt;a href="County%20Mayo"&gt;west coast&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href="Ireland"&gt;Ireland&lt;/a&gt;.

<h2>Understand</h2>
Achill is an island but is connected to the mainland of Ireland by a bridge at Achill Sound. The bridge spans about 100 metres and allows two lanes of traffic to pass onto the island.

The main villages of Achill are (from the west) Dooagh, Pollagh, Keel, Dookinella, The Valley, Bunacurry, Cashel, Dooega, Saula, Ashleam, Dereens, Cloughmore, Achill Sound and Currane.

<h2>Talk</h2>
They speak traditional &lt;a href="Irish"&gt;Irish&lt;/a&gt; as well as English.

<h2>Get in</h2>
You can get to Achill by car or bus. Two buses a day leave from Westport to Achill and back.

<h2>Get around</h2>

<h2>See</h2>

Achill has a beautiful little sandy beach - Keel Bay. The view from Menaun Heights towards this bay is spectacular.

<h2>Do</h2>
Various stunning beaches make this a popular holiday location for the locals.

<h2>Eat</h2>
<ul>
BULLET::::- &lt;bdi class="vcard"&gt; &lt;bdi class="listing-name"&gt;♡❤♡Bayside Bistro♡❤♡&lt;/bdi&gt;, &lt;bdi class="adr listing-address street-address"&gt;Keel&lt;/bdi&gt;, &lt;abbr title="phone" style="text-decoration:none"&gt;☏&lt;/abbr&gt; &lt;bdi class="tel listing-phone"&gt; +353 98 43798 &lt;/bdi&gt; . &lt;bdi class="note listing-content"&gt;Family friendly sea food restaurant.&lt;/bdi&gt;&lt;/bdi&gt;

</ul>
<h2>Drink</h2>

<h2>Sleep</h2>

